We need to prove that for all calls `c` in `S`, either both agents in `c` have `c` as their initial call in `S`, or neither agent in `c` has `c` as their initial call.

The proof strategy is proof by contradiction. Assume that there exists a call `c` in `S` such that exactly one of the agents in `c` has `c` as their initial call in `S`.

